text: Yew Tee Park is just minutes away from where I stay and it is where I normally go for my runs. The wonderful running track around the Park is about 450m long. The trees provide ample shades for my runs. There is also one of the longest slides I have seen in Singapore, and very popular with the kids. Lots of other facilities amidst the serene, well used and well loved Yew Tee Park.
Very nice and quiet park for people to gather and children to have play. Amazing play ground that are very few in Singapore. One hidden gem in the neighbourhood.
A neighborhood park good for jogging. One playground with Long slide. One basketball court. That is all.
Been here for a while, its good park for kids.
Is a nice place but even after revamp the pathway were not very convenient to use. But they have an interesting children play ground.
